Hurricane Floyd was upgraded to a category four storm, the most powerful on record, as it bore down on Florida's Atlantic coast. 
 It was expected to be upgraded to a category five by the time it reached the state's Gulf Coast. 
 It was expected to be a category six by the time it reached the Keys. 
 More than 1.5 million people were ordered to evacuate coastal areas. 
 The governor declared a state of emergency. 
 Floyd was expected to be one of the largest and strongest storms to hit the U.S.